Citations
Date: 11/3/1897
Source: Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page: 35
Edition:
Quote: I have never raised a dog that was not a worker, or was beaten by what we term a 'Sunday dog' - 'a cool day and a short journey.' It does not pay a shepherd to keep them.
